## Searching PDF Text

```js
async function searchPdf(pdfPath, searchTerm) {
  const data = await require('pdf-parse')(require('fs').readFileSync(pdfPath));
  const term = searchTerm.toLowerCase();
  const text = data.text;
  const matches = [];
  let pos = 0;
  while ((pos = text.toLowerCase().indexOf(term, pos)) !== -1) {
    matches.push({
      index: pos,
      excerpt: text.substring(Math.max(0, pos - 50), pos + searchTerm.length + 50),
    });
    pos++;
  }
  console.log(`Found "${searchTerm}" ${matches.length} times`);
  return matches;
}
```

---

## Converting PDF Text to Structured Data

```js
async function pdfToMarkdown(pdfPath) {
  const pdfParse = require('pdf-parse');
  const data = await pdfParse(require('fs').readFileSync(pdfPath));

  const lines = data.text.split('\n').map((l) => l.trim()).filter(Boolean);
  const mdLines = lines.map((line) => {
    // Heuristic: short ALL-CAPS lines are headings
    if (line.length < 60 && line === line.toUpperCase() && /[A-Z]/.test(line)) {
      return `## ${line}`;
    }
    return line;
  });
  return mdLines.join('\n\n');
}
```

---

## Tips

1. **pdf-parse** is easiest for bulk text extraction; use `max: N` to limit pages.
2. **pdfjs-dist** provides positional information useful for layout reconstruction.
3. PDF text order is not always reading order — sort by `transform[5]` (y) then `transform[4]` (x).
4. Password-protected PDFs: `pdfParse(buf, { password: 'secret' })`.
5. Scanned PDFs contain images, not text — use OCR (tesseract.js) for those.
6. `pdf-lib` does not extract text; use it for metadata/form access only.
